blocks.text: This chapter explains how HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) affects information sharing in mental health care.

sections.title: Information Sharing with Family and Friends

blocks.text: Healthcare providers can share information with family members or friends involved in an individual's care or payment for care, unless the individual objects.
If a person objects to sharing information, healthcare providers must respect this decision, except in certain emergency situations.

sections.title: Communication from Family to Healthcare Providers

blocks.text: HIPAA allows healthcare providers to listen to family members' concerns about a patient's condition, even if they cannot share information back without the patient's consent.
In emergency situations, healthcare providers can share necessary information to prevent or lessen a serious and imminent threat to health or safety.
